title: Grateful Dead Live at Winterland Arena on 1971-12-31
description:
Set 1

Dancin' In The Streets, Mr. Charlie, Brown Eyed Women, Beat It On Down The Line, You Win Again, Jack Straw, Sugaree, El Paso, Chinatown Shuffle, Tennessee Jed, Mexicali Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Next Time You See Me, Playin' In The Band, Loser, One More Saturday Night*

Set 2

Truckin'-> Drums-> The Other One-> Me & My Uncle-> The Other One, Jam-> Black Peter, Big River, The Same Thing, Ramble On Rose, Sugar Magnolia, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: Casey Jones

With Donna Godchaux * FM broadcast KSAN-San Francisco - Other artist(s): GD; NRPS; Yogi Phlegm

reviews.review_text:
Don't want to be treated,,this old way NFA>GDTRFB>NFA
There is a reason why many Heads find themselves in later years drawn to the Gospel of Jesus Christ.
Nobody gets it without a preacher but the release of this worlds burdens and cares is something any Dead Head has almost certainly experienced attending a Dead Show.
The Big Question is am I prepared to meet a Holy God when my time on this earth ends?
If sin is so terrible to God that He would send His own Son to pay its penalty then what type of person ought we to be here during on our sojourn here on earth.
Wow, the NFA reprise gets wild with Pig & Bob.
---Jerry just throwing it down like Lightning bolts!
I love the FM DJ who says a few words while we wait for the encore.

At last Thanks for all the hard work. I've been hoping for an upgrade for years (complete with Weir's NYE story). The annoying buzz/hum is gone. Probably my favorite New Years show of all, in part because of Pigpen, no DJG, and I was there. Casey Jones is my personal favorite. Incredible locomotion. Whew!
